Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for constructing maximum matchings in trees, which is a problem in graph theory. The most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with algorithmic techniques for solving problems in graphs. The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem of maximum matching also has connections to game theory, which is covered under cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The paper may also be relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as trees are a special type of graph and have geometric interpretations. Finally, the paper may be relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the algorithms presented may have applications in distributed computing environments.
